<subSubSection id="40F3908183EE06AE4309967E02D03C24" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C107FA6B4EBFA33AB9F91AD015431A2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B682192BB505A8BC8F4B60C43B332EF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
The noteworthy features of 
<taxonomicName id="90AE0C830524E2C5F48FC229A9731A34" authorityName="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityYear="2022" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Dendrocorticiopsis" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="AF5BD7F07099F7BBB8FFB00F82F86D0E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: (1) subiculum composed of a basal layer, with compact texture; (2) oily materials usually present in hymenial layer; (3) cystidia with resinous materials at apices; (4) shortly clavate to subclavate basidia; (5) ellipsoid to ovoid basidiospores measuring 5-7 
<normalizedToken id="B3CF22AB7404A8214BAED9953EC48E70" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.2-5.2 
<normalizedToken id="0A88000D6335C31EEA0D529C206E9537" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="6C7C3C2A514EDCBEF1B8B586317C52CA" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.90.84562.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690444" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="AEE5BBB2B1D159EEADB03F804559312A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="5E7AF44ECE88701F58DD145954BA2852" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Basidiomata of 
<taxonomicName id="7C9E96DE86A3C4892E554D09D4B7E21F" authorityName="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityYear="2022" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Dendrocorticiopsis" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="A0449BF23796A293862AE12995905401" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(holotype, WEI 20-166). Scale bar: 1 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
