<subSubSection id="76665D3342580E5AD8B473FDD87F71A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="notes">
<paragraph id="AB8A145DE2DBEE31A57F389024CAAA6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8652059F491A409328C07D089A7EFD1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Both of the ITS and 28S sequences BLAST results showed that 
<taxonomicName id="ED6F6C58CC5B8594B0907E72483D0696" authorityName="Sheng H. Wu, C. L. Wei &amp; S. H. He" authorityYear="2022" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Dendrocorticiopsis" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="7FCA93AA24F835CB1CD372AC45C3630E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Dendrocorticiopsis orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to the strain BCRC 36235 that is annotated as 
<taxonomicName id="35B0938C8AAA02DECB75F75A945886F4" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Ganodermataceae" genus="Ganoderma" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ganoderma applanatum" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="applanatum">
<emphasis id="430C3C191545B1E61735935D29BA17F4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Ganoderma applanatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pers.) Pat. in GenBank. According to personal communication with Bioresource Collection and Research Center (BCRC, Taiwan), the strain BCRC 36235 was indeed isolated from a 
<taxonomicName id="C01D7B2C6E1C36D135254E207BD87AD6" authorityName="P.A.Karsten" authorityYear="1881" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Ganodermataceae" genus="Ganoderma" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Ganoderma" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C85845934FBDD0079744EEBA7C6CC711" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Ganoderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen collected by Dr. Jin-Torng Peng in Nantou, Central Taiwan, on wood of 
<taxonomicName id="FBA158E5BECDED8A7FA684D7CCC91D68" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acacia confusa" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis id="200C5F0C1F463DEFCDF1F6DB06A0E6F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Acacia confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Merr. However, as suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="F8B3877E3C9838549061E953A568C4BE" author="Suldbold, J" journalOrPublisher="Bioinformatics (Oxford, England)" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B21" refString="Suldbold, J, 2017. Taxonomic re-evaluation of medicinal wood-decaying fungi: Abundisporus, Fomitopsis, and Ganoderma in Korea. Dissertation, Seoul National University." title="Taxonomic re-evaluation of medicinal wood-decaying fungi: Abundisporus, Fomitopsis, and Ganoderma in Korea. Dissertation, Seoul National University." year="2017">Suldbold (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, the ITS (EU232219) and 28S (EU232303) sequences of the strain BCRC 36235 are not true 
<taxonomicName id="6B73DA65278F7DC53EE335B7F3DF27F5" genus="G." lsidName="G. applanatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="applanatum">
<emphasis id="792FD9716FF44E1753512D01F68FAE7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">G. applanatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we supposed that the strain could be contaminated by 
<taxonomicName id="CD14D80C546797A52104BB9ACA6DF338" genus="D." lsidName="D. orientalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="9C98E1A67C4F1A60FA20A74DC976DD3C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">D. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is known to grow on 
<taxonomicName id="FFC994A260A4C8F3C6C93E248A425550" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acacia" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94BB6068FE20E7E7DA72DF2A8D54DDD9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Acacia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen He 4195 collected on 
<taxonomicName id="FCBCD78A935D49BAC7C3DEF4E35150B2" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Punctulariaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Castanopsis" order="Corticiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2D489170393D5D5E722D26017AF8E3F4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Castanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="84BA51BDD5613E43E28CC1B222146898" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
) from Jiangxi Province has slightly smaller basidiospores (L = 5.8 
<normalizedToken id="DBF6D1045FF8E47DECB0FDCE9EA2B279" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, W = 4.2 
<normalizedToken id="2DE2CEA9A59143B02FE41B094F86D2C0" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) than the holotype.
</paragraph>
